---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Best Locations for Maine Dispensaries | Maine Dispensary Guide" description="Guide to finding the best location for your Maine cannabis dispensary. Population, competition, zoning, and real estate analysis.">
  <article>
    <header>
      <h1>Best Locations for a Dispensary in Maine</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to choose the optimal location for your Maine cannabis dispensary</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Location is one of the most critical factors in dispensary success. Maine's diverse cities and towns offer different opportunities and challenges. This guide helps you evaluate and choose the best location.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Location Factors</h2>
      
      <h3>Population & Demographics</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Population density and growth trends</li>
        <li>Age distribution (target: 21+ adults)</li>
        <li>Income levels and economic stability</li>
        <li>Tourist population (seasonal boosts)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Competition</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Number of existing dispensaries</li>
        <li>Market saturation levels</li>
        <li>Distance from competitors</li>
        <li>Competitive differentiation opportunities</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Zoning & Regulations</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Local opt-in/opt-out status</li>
        <li>Allowed zones for cannabis businesses</li>
        <li>Distance requirements (schools, churches)</li>
        <li>Signage and advertising restrictions</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Accessibility</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Foot traffic and visibility</li>
        <li>Parking availability</li>
        <li>Public transportation access</li>
        <li>Highway accessibility</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Top Maine Markets</h2>
      
      <h3>Portland</h3>
      <p>Largest city, high population, tourist destination. Higher competition but largest market.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Population: 68,000+</li>
        <li>Competition: Moderate-High</li>
        <li>Real Estate: Premium pricing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Lewiston</h3>
      <p>Second largest city, growing market, more affordable than Portland.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Population: 36,000+</li>
        <li>Competition: Low</li>
        <li>Real Estate: Moderate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Bangor</h3>
      <p>Northern Maine hub, growing cannabis market, less competition.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Population: 32,000+</li>
        <li>Competition: Low-Moderate</li>
        <li>Real Estate: Affordable</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>South Portland</h3>
      <p>Portland metro area benefits, lower costs than Portland proper.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Population: 25,000+</li>
        <li>Competition: Moderate</li>
        <li>Real Estate: Moderate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Augusta</h3>
      <p>Capital city, state government presence, steady traffic.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Population: 19,000+</li>
        <li>Competition: Low</li>
        <li>Real Estate: Affordable</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Real Estate Considerations</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Recommendation</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Size</td><td>1,500-3,000 sq ft minimum</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Build-out</td><td>Budget for modifications</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Loading</td><td>Preferred for inventory</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Parking</td><td>Dedicated spots required</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Lease Terms</td><td>5+ years recommended</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Research Steps</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Research local zoning laws</li>
        <li>Visit potential areas in person</li>
        <li>Analyze competitor locations</li>
        <li>Calculate population reach</li>
        <li>Evaluate real estate options</li>
        <li>Consult with local officials</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Location determines success - research thoroughly</li>
        <li>Check local opt-in/opt-out status first</li>
        <li>Balance population with competition</li>
        <li>Budget for build-out costs</li>
        <li>Long-term leases (5+ years) recommended</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>Market conditions change. Verify current information with local authorities.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  section h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul, ol { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; }
</style>
